Change language parameter in weather API request
Updated the URL string in the EventsEditScreen to use English language ('en') instead of Czech ('cs') when making requests to the weather API. This change affects the language of the information retrieved, aligning the output to the application's primary language.

Change language parameter in weather API request
Updated the URL string in the EventsEditScreen to use Czech language ('cs') instead of English ('en') when making requests to the weather API. This change affects the language of the information retrieved, conforming the output to the requirements of the specific user demographic.

Add numeric and icon fields to metrics
Modified the metric layouts and screens by adding 'numeric' and 'icon' properties to various metric items. 'numeric' is used to determine whether a metric's value is numeric or not, and 'icon' is to provide an associated icon. Ensuring that applications handle metric values correctly and provide a more visually appealing and understandable representation to the users.

PATCH: Update icon color in metric view
Updated the icon color to primary in the metric view improving the visual appeal. This change is part of a larger effort to improve the user interface and enhance the user experience by improving readability and visual cohesion.

Refactor `EventsEditScreen` layout and improve metric display
The `EventsEditScreen` code responsible for layout generation has been refactored to enhance user-friendly interface. Additionally, the metric display functionality has been adjusted to only display a numerical prefix for metrics with numerical values, providing a cleaner and more intuitive display.
